The paper discusses optimization algorithms for large-scale problems in machine learning, specifically stochastic gradient descent. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions locality sensitive hashing (LSH), which is a technique used in data structures (cs.DS) and computer vision (cs.CV). The experiments conducted in the paper involve language representation models (cs.CL) and deep learning (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.AI.
